article.headline: Troy 94, South Alabama 70
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. -- Kenny Ware scored 20 points and Troy defeated South Alabama 94-70 on Thursday night. Ware, who was 6 of 10 from the field and 6-for-8 from 3-point range, led the Trojans, who shot 50 percent as a team (32 of 63). Brandon Hazzard also had a hot hand from beyond the arc for the Trojans (8-10, 3-3 Sun Belt Conference), going 4-for-6. Troy shot 53.3 percent from 3-point range (16 of 30), including hitting 10 of 17 long-range shots in the first half (58.8 percent). Richard Delk added 17 points, seven rebounds, six assists and three steals for Troy. Bryan Sherrer led South Alabama (10-7, 3-3) with 14 points, as he went 5-for-5 from the free-throw line. The Trojans held the Jaguars' two all-conference players, Domonic Tilford and Brandon Davis to just four and two points, respectively, as they took a 47-29 first-half lead.
